How to install
    1. Install the latest Python version at https://www.python.org/downloads/
        Make sure to check the option to add Python to the path.

    2. Download and extract the project
        https://github.com/stlxiii/TwitterScraper/archive/master.zip

    3. Open a command line / terminal at the extracted "TwitterScraper-master" folder

    4. Run the following commands to install a virtual environement
        python -m venv .venv
        .venv\Scripts\activate.bat       (or .venv\Scripts\activate if not on PC)
        pip install --upgrade pip
        pip install -r requirements.txt

    5. Install Firefox and the Firefox webdriver
        https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases
        You can place the webdriver file in ".venv/bin"
        or anywhere else in the system path

How to use:
    1. Enter URLs of tweets in config.ini
    
    2. Run download.py
       It may be necessary to run it several times until no
       new tweets are found.

    3. Run export.py
       Tweet information will be saved under /export/{tweet id}.csv